                     <unitdate unitdatetype="inclusive">1813 Noc 23</unitdate>
                     <container containerid="39002094500338"
                                id="aspace_3c11e7f4d2c60f62963e5f9c6cd33eea"
                                label="Mixed Materials"
                                localtype="box">1</container>
                  </did>
                  <scopecontent id="aspace_8785423bd4177c8108fb42bf37ba2bb3">
                     <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                     <p>Mavesyn-Ridware <lb/> 3 p.; 23 x 18 cm. <lb/> d 1/42</p>
                  </scopecontent>
               </c>
            </c>
            <c id="ref16" level="subseries">
               <did>
                  <unittitle>HERBERT, SIR HENRY, 1595-1673</unittitle>
               </did>
               <c id="ref17" level="file">
                  <did>
                     <unittitle>Memorandum: autograph MS</unittitle>
                     <unitdate unitdatetype="inclusive">[1630 or later]</unitdate>
                     <container containerid="39002094500338"
                                id="aspace_f3eb2098ee2051a141a8e649bc500adc"
                                label="Mixed Materials"
                                localtype="box">1</container>
                  </did>
                  <scopecontent id="aspace_238749bbd68ce57d96f35e7d403ea43b">
                     <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                     <p>1 p.; 12 x 10 cm. <lb/> Lists holders of the office of the <lb/> Master of the Revels from 1569-1630; <lb/> in the same volume (Osborn Shelves <lb/> d 1/185) is a fragment of an <lb/> autograph license issued by Herbert, <lb/> dated 1636 Jul 12, as well as a <lb/> document concerning disbursements of <lb/> the Revels Office signed by Herbert's <lb/> assistants (Osborn Shelves <lb/> d 1/176-180). <lb/> d 1/156; d 1/185; d 1/176-180</p>
                  </scopecontent>
               </c>
            </c>
            <c id="ref19" level="subseries">
               <did>
                  <unittitle>HERBERT, SIR HENRY, 1595-1673</unittitle>
               </did>
               <c id="ref20" level="file">
                  <did>
                     <unittitle>Letter (draft) to Henry Hyde, 2nd earl of Clarendon (1638-1709) and Edward Montagu, 2nd earl of Manchester (1602-1671)</unittitle>
                     <unitdate unitdatetype="inclusive">1662 Jul 11</unitdate>
                     <container containerid="39002094500338"
                                id="aspace_c2d47d7b5900c1a93ec1b03d1c17be43"
                                label="Mixed Materials"
                                localtype="box">1</container>
                  </did>
                  <scopecontent id="aspace_17900244fb058dfdb8453069c255e982">
                     <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                     <p>Cary-house <lb/> 2 p.; 29 x 19 cm. <lb/> Lists fees and profits of the office <lb/> of the Master of the Revels and <lb/> mentions his differences with Sir <lb/> William D'Avenant (1606-1668). <lb/> d 1/227-230</p>
                  </scopecontent>
               </c>
            </c>
